Li  Liu is a first-year master student in Computational Social Science at the University of Chicago. He works as a research assistant for the data analytics division at the Harris School of Public Policy. Previously, he held teaching assistant position for MBA statistics course at the Booth School of Business. He had interned at organizations in e-commerce, media, education, and sales. He is enthusiastic about making data-driven decisions for business using machine learning, data mining, and causal inference. He earned a B.S. in applied mathematics and B.A. in Economics from Indiana University Bloomington from 2015 to 2018. His hometown is Shanghai, China.
